BER Reduces Its Economic Growth Estimate for South Africa in 2011 to 3.7%

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-05-27T06:20:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/ber-reduces-its-2011-economic-growth-estimate-for-south-africa-to-3-7-.html
South Africa ’s Bureau For Economic
Research reduced its forecast for economic growth in the
continent’s largest economy to 3.7 percent from 3.8 percent, the
bureau, based at the University of Stellenbosch, near  Cape Town ,
said in a report handed to reporters in Johannesburg today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  